  "question": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?",
  "prompt": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "160",
  "generated_text": "To solve this problem, we need to calculate the total time Carla spends downloading the file, including the interruption caused by the restart.\n\n**Step 1: Calculate the time taken to download the first part.**\nCarla downloads at a rate of 2 GB/minute.\nThe file size is 200 GB.\nThe interruption occurs at 40% of the way through.\nFirst, calculate the size of the first part:\n$$ \\text{Size}_1 = 200 \\text{ GB} \\times 0.40 = 80 \\text{ GB} $$\n\nNext, calculate the time it takes to download this first part:\n$$ \\text{Time}_1 = \\frac{\\text{Size}_1}{\\text{Rate}} = \\frac{80 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 40 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Step 2: Calculate the time taken for the restart.**\nThe restart takes 20 minutes.\n$$ \\text{Time}_{\\text{restart}} = 20 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Step 3: Calculate the time taken to download the second part.**\nAfter the restart, the download must begin from the beginning. However, since the download rate is constant, the time required to download the remaining 60% (which is $200 \\text{ GB} - 80 \\text{ GB} = 120 \\text{ GB}$) will be the same as the time it took to download the first 80 GB.\nAlternatively, since the rate is 2 GB/min:\n$$ \\text{Time}_2 = \\frac{200 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 100 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Step 4: Calculate the total time.**\nThe total time is the sum of the time for the first part, the restart time, and the time for the second part.\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = \\text{Time}_1 + \\text{Time}_{\\text{restart}} + \\text{Time}_2 $$\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = 40 \\text{ min} + 20 \\text{ min} + 100 \\text{ min} $$\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = 160 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n\\boxed{160}\n",
